      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of \"paramount\" doesn't mean religious freedom is erased, but rather that it must operate within the framework of civil law. The state's duty to protect all citizens equally through universal laws is the bedrock of a functioning democracy. Religious freedom is robust, but it is not absolute and must yield when it directly conflicts with the fundamental, non-negotiable duties of citizenship.",
      "source": "target",
